        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 22 at 10:04PM CDT by NWS Des Moines IA</headline>
        <description>At 1004 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm
over Mount Ayr, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mount Ayr, Kellerton, Benton, Delphos, Beaconsfield and Mt Ayr
Municipal Airport.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
